declare_parcel_as_script_with_stdin <<'/---'
Handle *`zsh` module* aliases.
/---

# ....................{ LOADERS                            }....................
#FIXME: Add examples. Essential here, due to the complexity.

declare_alias_with_stdin 'void :load_module_mapfile_start(void)'\
    ':load_module_mapfile
    :try {' <<'/---'
Load `zsh` module `mapfile` before an expansion of :load_module_mapfile_start()
in the same syntactic context guaranteeably unloads such module. See
:load_module_mapfile() for further details.
/---

declare_alias_with_stdin 'void :load_module_mapfile_stop(void)'\
    '} always :{
        :unload_module_mapfile
    }:' <<'/---'
Unload `zsh` module `mapfile` after an expansion of :load_module_mapfile_start()
in the same syntactic context loads such module, even if another command fails
or throws an exception between that and this expansion. See
:unload_module_mapfile() for further details.
/---

# --------------------( WASTELANDS                         )--------------------
